Atomictalk is an extension to [http://code.google.com/p/aspectxml/ AspectXML] that uses a Smalltalk influenced syntax for dynamically declaring, evaluating, and weaving content within a web page.  Atomictalk is built on top of an MVC framework similar to that made popular by Ruby on Rails, though [http://heim.ifi.uio.no/~trygver/themes/mvc/mvc-index.html originally introduced] as a programming model for Smalltalk by [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trygve_Reenskaug Trygve Reenskaug]. 
